    "what_description": "Ascogrammitis anfractuosa is a species of fern in the family Polypodiaceae. It is a rhizomatous, terrestrial fern with a stipe that is brown and hairy, and a lamina that is 10-40 cm long and 5-15 cm wide, with an obtuse to acute apex, and a pinnate to bipinnate leaf arrangement. The lamina has a rachis that is brown and hairy, and pinnae that are lanceolate to elliptic in shape, with an acute to obtuse apex. The sori are marginal, and the spores are yellow-brown in color, with a diameter of 40-60 \u03bcm. Ascogrammitis anfractuosa is found in tropical and subtropical regions, typically in shaded, humid areas.",
