    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Ascogrammitis anfractuosa are derived from its leaves and include tea, made by steeping 1-2 teaspoons of dried leaves in 1 cup of boiling water for 5-10 minutes to treat digestive issues and reduce inflammation. Tincture is prepared by soaking 1 part of leaves in 2-3 parts of ethanol or glycerin for several weeks, then straining and diluting to treat various health conditions. Infusion involves steeping 1-2 teaspoons of fresh or dried leaves in 1 cup of boiling water for 5-10 minutes to treat fever, cough, and sore throat. Salve is prepared by infusing the leaves in oil and mixing with beeswax to treat skin irritations and wounds, while decoction is made by boiling 1-2 teaspoons of dried leaves in 1 cup of water for 10-15 minutes to treat urinary issues and kidney problems. These preparations are used due to the plant's reported antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, and antimicrobial properties.",
